<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Email Basics for Job Search</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="./email.css">
</head>
<body>

   
    <header>
        <div class="logo-title">
            <img src="logo/email.webp" alt="Email Logo" class="logo">
            <h1>Email Basics for Job Search</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="tagline">Learn how to create, send, and manage emails to improve your job opportunities.</p>
    </header>

    
    <section class="intro">
        <h2>What is Email?</h2>
        <p>Email (Electronic Mail) is a digital method of sending and receiving messages instantly across the world. 
           It is one of the most important tools for professional communication, including job applications and networking.</p>
    </section>

   
    <section class="importance">
        <h2>Why Email is Important for Job Search</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Send resumes and cover letters to employers.</li>
            <li>Receive interview invitations and updates.</li>
            <li>Subscribe to job alerts on different platforms.</li>
            <li>Communicate professionally with HR managers and recruiters.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

   
    <section class="steps">
        <h2>Step-by-Step: Creating and Using Email</h2>

        <div class="step">
            <img src="/logo/create.webp" alt="Create Email Account">
            <div>
                <h3>1. Create an Email Account</h3>
                <p>Visit email service websites like <a href="https://mail.google.com" target="_blank">Gmail</a>, 
                   <a href="https://outlook.live.com" target="_blank">Outlook</a>, or Yahoo Mail. 
                   Click on "Sign Up" and follow the steps to create your account.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <img src="/logo/inbox.webp" alt="Email Inbox Example">
            <div>
                <h3>2. Understand Your Inbox</h3>
                <p>Your inbox shows all incoming emails. Unread messages are usually bold or marked. 
                   Always check for important emails from job portals and recruiters.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
            <img src="logo/jobAlert.png" alt="Job Alert Email Example">
            <div>
                <h3>3. Sending Professional Emails</h3>
                <p>Click "Compose" to write a new email. Use a clear subject line, professional greeting, and concise message.
                   Attach your resume or portfolio when applying for jobs.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

   
    <section class="tips">
        <h2>Professional Email Tips</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Use a professional email address (avoid nicknames).</li>
            <li>Check your email daily for responses.</li>
            <li>Keep your language formal and polite.</li>
            <li>Double-check attachments before sending.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    
